Durban – Three men were arrested for drug possession in three different police operations in a bid to stop drugs in the eThekwini Inner South Cluster. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said on Tuesday, Crime Intelligence members followed up on information about someone who had bought drugs in Bayview. “Information led the members to Isipingo area where they spotted a suspicious looking suspect fitting the same description given to them. He was searched and found in possession of 1 290 pink and clear capsules of heroin to the street value of R38 700,” Zwane said. He said the man was arrested and charged for possession of drugs. “On the same day, Chatsworth Drug Squad arrested a 42-year-old man at Moorton area, Chatsworth after he was found in possession of an unlicensed firearm with ammunition as well as 37 pink and clear capsules of heroin. The suspect was charged accordingly. The members proceeded to Southway Mall where they arrested a 25-year-old man for possession of 10 grams of cocaine to the street value of R21 000,” he said. He said all the men will appear in the Chatsworth Magistrate’s Court on Thursday. Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, said: “I appeal to the community members to break the silence and report drug related cases in their areas. Our police officers will act decisively against those who are dealing or using drugs in the province.” Daily News